original: Eriksson, Göta Margareta, läroverksadjunkt, Skara, f. 3/8/17 i Gbg av dir. Carl E. o. Göta Hällström. — Studiex. i Gbg 36, fil. kand. i Lund 40, fil. mag. 41, provår v. Gbgs foliksk:-sem. 47. Tjg. v. Malmö borgarsk. 40, Gbgs flicklärov. 42, i Töreboda 42-44, e. adj. v. Skara h. a. k ’sed. 44.
translated: Eriksson, Göta Margareta, high school teacher, Skara, born August 3, 1917 in Gothenburg to director Carl E. and Göta Hällström. She completed her secondary school studies in Gothenburg in 1936, earned a Bachelor of Arts degree in Lund in 1940 and a Master of Arts degree in 1941. She also worked as a trainee at the Gothenburg people's school seminar in 1947. She worked at Malmö burgess school in 1940, Gothenburg girls' high school in 1942, in Töreboda from 1942-1944, and as an assistant teacher at Skara higher domestic science school since 1944.
